Class LoginController

  • java.lang.Object
    • application.LoginController

  • public class LoginController
extends java.lang.Object
    This class allows the user to login to their account and takes them to the manager main page if they are a amanager, or a waiter main page otherwise.

    • Method Detail

      • ManagerLogin

        public void ManagerLogin(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
                  throws java.lang.Exception
        This method first checks whether the input boxes are blank in which case a error message is displayed. If data has been entered, the input username is checked against the stored username for that user and the same is done for the password. If the input text matches the username and password pair for the current user, the manager main page is opened.
        Parameters:
        event - the event
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - the exception
